{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Implement the Miscarriage Patient Charter in England, as in Scotland",
        "additional_details": "Scotland already benefits from the Miscarriage Patient Charter, but patients in England do not have the same guaranteed standards of care. This creates inequality and inconsistency at a vulnerable time. Implementing the charter in England would ensure fair, compassionate, and consistent support for all, regardless of location.",
        "background": "The Government should implement the Miscarriage Patient Charter in England, matching the standard already in Scotland. This should ensure consistent, compassionate care, clear communication, access to information, and appropriate support for anyone experiencing miscarriage.",
